This paper deals with a dynamic data structure for maintaining a vertex coloring of a graph, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithms. The paper presents a new data structure that achieves a constant amortized update time, which is a significant improvement over the previous best result of O(log Delta) expected amortized update time. Therefore, the paper is likely to be relevant to several subfields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), machine learning (cs.LG), and distributed computing (cs.DC).
